// Content Sprint 10: Reporting, Performance and Marketplace Operations.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_10 = {"operator-dashboard":{"summary":"Use the Operator Dashboard as the marketplace’s daily starting point, review work requiring attention, identify operational risks and move into the detailed queues where action is completed.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Customer service","Catalogue","Finance","Seller management","Technology"],"sections":{"Understand the Operator Dashboard":"<p>The Operator Dashboard is the first page displayed after signing in to the Operator Portal. It brings together operational work requiring attention, previous-day trading results, Problem Reports and Marketplacer system status.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Review the Dashboard</strong><p>Identify the queues and risks requiring attention.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Open the detailed queue</strong><p>Use Review now to move to the relevant operational page.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Investigate and act</strong><p>Apply filters, review the underlying records and complete the required action.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Confirm ownership</strong><p>Resolve, assign or deliberately monitor every material item.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the Dashboard to identify where attention is needed.</strong> Use the destination page to understand and resolve each item.</div><p>The Dashboard supports the daily routine, but it does not replace detailed reports, integration monitoring, finance reconciliation or Seller performance review.</p>","Awaiting Action":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Dashboard tile</th><th>What it highlights</th><th>Typical destination</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Products to review</strong></td><td>Products awaiting Operator vetting</td><td>Adverts → Product Vetting</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Items not dispatched</strong></td><td>Seller Invoice items not yet fulfilled</td><td>Orders → Not Dispatched</td></tr><tr><td><strong>New chat messages</strong></td><td>Unread Seller conversations</td><td>Sellers → Chat</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Payouts to approve</strong></td><td>Seller Invoice payments awaiting release</td><td>Orders → Payouts to Approve</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Refund requests</strong></td><td>Refund Requests requiring review or monitoring</td><td>Orders → Refund Requests</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The counts are shortcuts into each queue. A low count does not prove that the underlying process is healthy. Open the destination and review the records before deciding whether action is required.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Tile</th><th>Primary owner</th><th>Supporting team</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Products to review</td><td>Catalogue operations</td><td>Seller management</td></tr><tr><td>Items not dispatched</td><td>Marketplace operations</td><td>Seller management</td></tr><tr><td>New chat messages</td><td>Seller support</td><td>Operations or Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Payouts to approve</td><td>Finance</td><td>Marketplace operations</td></tr><tr><td>Refund requests</td><td>Customer service or Operations</td><td>Finance and Seller management</td></tr><tr><td>Problem reports</td><td>Technology or Operations</td><td>Integration partner</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Products to Review":"<p>Select <strong>Review now</strong> to open <strong>Adverts → Product Vetting</strong>.</p><p>Review Category, Brand, titles, descriptions, images, Variants, required attributes, Catalog Rules and marketplace policy. Prioritise launch blockers, campaign products, resubmissions and ageing submissions.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not bulk approve only to clear the Dashboard count.</strong> Use bulk approval only when the products have already been validated through the approved quality process.</div><p>Approved products move through asynchronous publication processing, so they may not appear immediately on the customer-facing storefront.</p>","Items Not Dispatched":"<p>Select <strong>Review now</strong> to open the Not Dispatched view. Review Seller, Seller Invoice, payment date, Line Items, quantities, Seller dispatch SLA, Carrier, tracking requirements and integration status.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Operator response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Within dispatch SLA</td><td>Continue monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Approaching SLA</td><td>Remind or contact the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>SLA breached</td><td>Escalate through Seller performance management</td></tr><tr><td>Seller cannot fulfil</td><td>Coordinate cancellation</td></tr><tr><td>Dispatched externally but not synchronised</td><td>Investigate fulfilment integration</td></tr><tr><td>Order should not have reached the Seller</td><td>Investigate Order creation and routing</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>An undispatched item is not automatically overdue. Compare the payment date with the effective Seller SLA and review the underlying Order before escalating.</p>","New Chat Messages":"<p>Select <strong>Review now</strong> to open the Seller chat area. Chat is useful for quick onboarding, product, Order, fulfilment and refund questions.</p><p>Define monitoring hours, response expectations, handover ownership and the types of issue that must be moved into email, a case-management system, an incident record or a Support ticket.</p><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>A cleared chat count should mean every message is answered, resolved or transferred into an owned follow-up process.</strong></div>","Payouts to Approve":"<p>Select <strong>Review now</strong> to review Seller Invoice payments awaiting release. Before approval, confirm the Invoice is legitimate and complete, financial values are correct, no unresolved dispute should hold payment and the Seller’s payout details are valid.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The Seller Invoice is complete</li><li>Operator payment release has been approved</li><li>The remittance delay has passed</li><li>The Seller schedule is due</li><li>The eligible Seller balance is positive</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Releasing payment is a financial control, not a routine click-through task.</strong></div><p>Automatic payout approval can reduce the number of records shown, but Finance must still reconcile Remittance Advices, Invoice Amendments, negative balances and actual Seller payments.</p>","Refund Requests":"<p>Select <strong>Review now</strong> to open <strong>Orders → Refund Requests</strong>. The Dashboard count groups several workflow positions together, so open the detailed queue and review each request.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Typical meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Awaiting</strong></td><td>Seller, return or Operator action remains</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Processed</strong></td><td>Ready for Operator financial finalisation</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Refunded</strong></td><td>Marketplacer workflow has been finalised</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Denied</strong></td><td>Every affected Refund Request Line Item was denied</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Prioritise Processed requests, aged Awaiting requests, returns delivered but not assessed, payment failures, disputed denials and refunds affecting imminent Seller payouts.</p>","Yesterday’s Trading":"<p>The previous-day snapshot displays Orders, Invoices, Average Order Value, Total Sales and Total Commission. Select <strong>View full performance insights</strong> for broader reporting.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Observation</th><th>Follow-up</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Orders fall unexpectedly</td><td>Check storefront, payment and Order integrations</td></tr><tr><td>Orders rise but Invoices rise faster</td><td>Review multi-Seller basket composition</td></tr><tr><td>Average Order Value changes materially</td><td>Review product mix, promotions and campaigns</td></tr><tr><td>Total Sales differs from ecommerce reporting</td><td>Compare scope, status and date definitions</td></tr><tr><td>Commission appears low</td><td>Review Commission Packages and financial adjustments</td></tr><tr><td>No trading appears</td><td>Confirm the marketplace traded and reporting is current</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The snapshot is directional. Do not use it as the sole basis for month-end reporting, Seller payment or executive finance reporting.</p>","Problem Reports":"<p>Problem Reports can point to failed or unexpected processing involving webhooks, integrations, background jobs, imports, Orders or fulfilment updates. Open the report before deciding whether the issue is transient, recovered or requires intervention.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Transient and recovered</td><td>Record and continue monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Repeated failure</td><td>Investigate integration or configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Order or payment affected</td><td>Escalate immediately</td></tr><tr><td>Seller-specific integration issue</td><td>Contact the Seller or integration owner</td></tr><tr><td>Platform behaviour unclear</td><td>Raise a Marketplacer Support request</td></tr><tr><td>Duplicate or stale report</td><td>Confirm current object state before acting</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Review first and latest occurrence, failure count, affected Seller or integration, object IDs, payload and error details, retries and customer impact. Do not retry payment, Order creation or refund processing blindly.</p>","System Status":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Indicator</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Green</strong></td><td>Fully operational</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Yellow</strong></td><td>Some issues are occurring</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Red</strong></td><td>Major performance issues</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>When the indicator is yellow or red, review the affected services, pause risky retries, notify internal stakeholders and reconcile delayed records after recovery.</p><p>A green status does not prove that every webhook, Seller integration, payment, Order or background task succeeded. Continue using Problem Reports and integration monitoring.</p>","Dashboard Permissions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Work area</th><th>Permission</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller chat</td><td>Manage chat</td></tr><tr><td>Orders and Not Dispatched</td><td>View orders</td></tr><tr><td>Payout approval</td><td>Manage orders</td></tr><tr><td>Refund queue</td><td>View refund requests</td></tr><tr><td>Return processing</td><td>Process returns</td></tr><tr><td>Refund finalisation</td><td>Process refunds</td></tr><tr><td>Product Vetting</td><td>Manage product catalog</td></tr><tr><td>Performance Insights</td><td>View performance report</td></tr><tr><td>Problem Reports</td><td>View problem reports</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A user may see a Dashboard count but still lack permission to complete the underlying action. Test each custom role using the intended user account.</p>","Daily Dashboard Routine":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Check System Status</strong><p>Identify platform-wide incidents before working transaction queues.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Review Problem Reports</strong><p>Confirm whether current failures affect customers or Sellers.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Review customer-critical work</strong><p>Prioritise Orders, fulfilment and refunds.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Review Seller-critical work</strong><p>Respond to chat and follow up undispatched items.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Review catalogue work</strong><p>Process launch blockers and ageing Product Vetting items.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Review financial approvals</strong><p>Apply payout controls and resolve exceptions.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><div><strong>Review trading</strong><p>Investigate unusual previous-day movement.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><div><strong>Record owners and handover</strong><p>Move unresolved work into an owned operational record.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Work</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Critical</strong></td><td>Platform incidents, failed Orders, failed payments and customer refund failures</td></tr><tr><td><strong>High</strong></td><td>Overdue dispatch, Processed refunds and payout exceptions</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Medium</strong></td><td>Seller messages, return assessments and launch blockers</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Routine</strong></td><td>Standard Product Vetting, trading review and non-urgent follow-up</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Test the Operator Dashboard":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The Dashboard loads for each intended Operator role</li><li>Every Awaiting action tile opens the correct destination</li><li>A product submitted for vetting appears in Products to review</li><li>An undispatched test Order appears in Items not dispatched</li><li>A Seller chat creates a new-message notification</li><li>A manual payout approval appears where expected</li><li>A Refund Request appears in the refund queue</li><li>Yesterday’s trading updates after completed test activity</li><li>Problem Reports are available only to authorised users</li><li>Resolving a record updates the relevant queue</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Every Dashboard tile has an assigned owner</li><li>Monitoring frequency is documented</li><li>Dispatch, refund and Product Vetting SLAs are defined</li><li>Seller chat response expectations are agreed</li><li>Payout approval authority is restricted</li><li>Processed refunds have a finalisation owner</li><li>Problem Reports have a Technology or Operations owner</li><li>System Status escalation is documented</li><li>Operator roles are tested</li><li>Yesterday’s trading is not treated as a finance ledger</li><li>Unresolved work is captured outside the Dashboard</li><li>Daily and shift-handover routines are established</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27307693304333-Operator-welcome-screen-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator welcome screen overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741316387725-Review-and-approve-products-adverts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and approve products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator user role permissions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599850695821-Intro-to-the-Seller-Performance-dashboard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Intro to the Seller Performance dashboard</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["daily-operations","Daily Marketplace Operations"],["sales-reporting","Sales Reporting"],["seller-performance-reporting","Seller Performance Reporting"],["finance-reporting-operations","Finance Reporting"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"]]},"sales-reporting":{"summary":"Use Marketplacer’s sales reports to investigate transactions, reconcile customer Orders with Seller Invoices, analyse Seller and Category performance, and select the correct date and financial fields for each reporting purpose.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Finance","Customer service","Seller management","Commercial","Data and Technology"],"sections":{"Choose the Right Reporting View":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Reporting view</th><th>Best used for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Orders → All Sales</strong></td><td>Transaction searches, Order investigation, Invoice details and CSV extracts</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Reporting → Sales Report</strong></td><td>Summarised marketplace Sales</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Reporting → Seller Summary</strong></td><td>Seller-level review and export</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Reporting → Performance Insights</strong></td><td>Trends and headline marketplace metrics</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Reporting → Remittances</strong></td><td>Processed and unprocessed Seller payment records</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Orders → Refund Requests</strong></td><td>Operational refund workflow</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Refunds Report</strong></td><td>Detailed refund and financial reconciliation</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Start with the business question, then choose the report, date field and financial measure that answer it.</strong></div>","Use the All Sales Report":"<p>Go to <strong>Orders → All Sales</strong>. Use All Sales to investigate customer Orders, Seller Invoices, products, quantities, customer and Seller details, statuses, prices, tax, discounts, postage, commission, merchant fees, payments, Shipments, refunds, remittance values and external IDs.</p><p>It is the primary transaction-level report for questions such as whether an Order reached Marketplacer, which Seller owns an Invoice, what commission was charged, whether the Seller dispatched and why marketplace totals differ from another system.</p><p>Use recurring analytical tools for executive trend reporting rather than repeatedly treating a raw transaction extract as a finished report.</p>","Search and Filter Sales":"<p>Filter by Order number, Invoice number, Order or Invoice status, Created, Completed, Paid or Remitted dates and delivery type. Customer filters include name, phone, email and IP address. Seller filters include Seller, Account Manager and Sales Agent.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Search by Invoice number where available</li><li>Use External ID for cross-system reconciliation</li><li>Use Order number for the complete customer purchase</li><li>Use customer email only when stronger identifiers are unavailable</li></ul><p>One customer Order can contain several Seller Invoices. Use both the Marketplacer identifier and the connected system’s external identifier.</p>","Customise and Export the Report":"<p>Use <strong>Show / hide table columns</strong> to select only the fields needed for the task.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Operational set</th><th>Finance set</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Created, Paid and Completed dates; Order and Invoice numbers; Seller; customer; product; SKU; quantity; Shipment; tracking; refund and external ID</td><td>Order and Invoice numbers; Seller; customer paid; Invoice total; item and postage values; tax; discounts; commission; merchant fees; refunds; remittance; payment gateway and transaction ID</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>After filtering, request the CSV through <strong>Email results</strong>. Retain the original file, extraction date and filters. Use the API, webhooks, Snowflake or another approved pipeline where recurring manual extraction will not scale.</p>","Understand Orders, Invoices and Line Items":"<div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\"><strong>Customer Order</strong><br>One marketplace checkout</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\"><strong>Seller Invoice</strong><br>One record per Seller in the Order</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\"><strong>Line Item</strong><br>Purchased Variant and quantity</div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Question</th><th>Correct measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>How many customer checkouts occurred?</td><td>Distinct Order numbers</td></tr><tr><td>How many Seller fulfilment records were created?</td><td>Distinct Invoice numbers</td></tr><tr><td>How many different purchased records exist?</td><td>Line Items or distinct Variants</td></tr><tr><td>How many units were purchased?</td><td>Sum of quantity</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Order count, Invoice count, Line Item count and unit count are different measures.</strong></div>","Prevent Double Counting":"<p>Determine the reporting grain before calculating totals. One row may represent an Order, Seller Invoice, Line Item, Shipment or Invoice Amendment.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Recommended method</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Orders</td><td>Count distinct Order number</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Invoices</td><td>Count distinct Invoice number</td></tr><tr><td>Products sold</td><td>Count Line Items or distinct Variant IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Units sold</td><td>Sum quantity</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice revenue</td><td>Sum once per distinct Invoice</td></tr><tr><td>Product revenue</td><td>Sum approved item-level values</td></tr><tr><td>Commission</td><td>Use the appropriate commission field at the correct grain</td></tr><tr><td>Refunds</td><td>Use Refund Request or Invoice Amendment data without duplicate inclusion</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>If a $150 Invoice total repeats on three Line Item rows, the correct Invoice value is $150, not $450. Validate a sample of known Orders against the Portal before publishing a report.</p>","Report on Seller Sales":"<p>Use All Sales for detailed Seller investigation and Seller Summary, Sales Report or Performance Insights for higher-level comparison.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Business question</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Total item Sales</td><td>How much product value did the Seller generate?</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice count</td><td>How many Seller fulfilment records were created?</td></tr><tr><td>Unit count</td><td>How many units were sold?</td></tr><tr><td>Average Invoice value</td><td>What is the average Seller-specific transaction size?</td></tr><tr><td>Commission</td><td>How much marketplace revenue did the Seller generate?</td></tr><tr><td>Refund value</td><td>How much value was later refunded?</td></tr><tr><td>Net Sales</td><td>What remains after the approved refund treatment?</td></tr><tr><td>Remitted value</td><td>How much entered the Seller payout process?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Define each measure in the reporting dictionary before comparing Sellers.</p>","Report on Category and Product Sales":"<p>Export Advert ID, product name, Variant, SKU, quantity, Category, Brand, item price, discounts and commission for Category, Brand, product and Variant analysis.</p><p>Retain stable Category and Brand IDs alongside names because labels can change. Confirm which Category level the exported value represents and maintain the full hierarchy for repeatable reporting.</p><p>For a mixed storefront, combine Marketplacer Seller data with first-party Sales before describing the result as total business Sales.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Sales by Category and Brand</li><li>Units by product and Variant</li><li>Commission by Category</li><li>Refund and cancellation concentration</li><li>Seller dependency by Category</li><li>Sales per live stocked product</li></ul>","Choose the Correct Date":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>What it represents</th><th>Common use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Created at</strong></td><td>Order record creation</td><td>Integration monitoring and checkout activity</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Completed at</strong></td><td>Completed customer purchase</td><td>Sales reporting</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Paid at</strong></td><td>Payment completion</td><td>Payment and Finance reconciliation</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Shipment date</strong></td><td>Seller dispatch</td><td>Fulfilment and SLA reporting</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Remit after</strong></td><td>Remittance delay passed</td><td>Future payment eligibility</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Remitted Date</strong></td><td>Included in remittance processing</td><td>Seller payment reporting</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Refund Date</strong></td><td>Refund finalisation</td><td>Refund and net-Sales reporting</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Created Date can include Orders that did not complete payment. Completed Date does not mean the Seller dispatched. Use a separate date for each business event.</p>","Understand Remittance Dates":"<p><strong>Remit after</strong> is the earliest date the configured delay has passed. It does not prove payment release, a due schedule, a positive balance, a generated Remittance Advice or actual bank payment.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Event date</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Completed at</td><td>Customer purchase</td></tr><tr><td>Shipment date</td><td>Seller fulfilment</td></tr><tr><td>Remit after</td><td>Delay eligibility</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Advice Date</td><td>Remittance processing</td></tr><tr><td>External payout date</td><td>Actual transfer of funds</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use processed remittance records with the external payout system to confirm whether the Seller was actually paid.</p>","Include Refunds and Adjustments":"<p>Sales can change after the original Order through cancellations, returns, partial refunds, postage refunds, commission adjustments, merchant-fee adjustments, Invoice Amendments and credit notes.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Gross Sales</td><td>Original approved Sales before later refunds</td></tr><tr><td>Refund value</td><td>Customer cancellations and returns</td></tr><tr><td>Net Sales</td><td>Gross Sales less the approved refund treatment</td></tr><tr><td>Gross commission</td><td>Original commission</td></tr><tr><td>Commission adjustment</td><td>Commission reversed or retained through amendments</td></tr><tr><td>Net commission</td><td>Commission after amendments</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Document whether each field includes tax, postage, discounts and refunds, and whether it represents the customer, Seller or Operator perspective. Do not subtract refunds from a field that already includes them.</p><p>Decide whether refunds are attributed to the original Sale period or the refund-finalisation period, then apply the rule consistently.</p>","Reconcile External Systems":"<div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Storefront Order</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Marketplacer Order and Seller Invoices</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Payment gateway</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller fulfilment system</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Refund workflow</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Remittance and payout system</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Accounting platform</div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Difference</th><th>What to check</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Storefront has more Sales</td><td>First-party items may not exist in Marketplacer</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer has more Invoices than storefront Orders</td><td>One Order splits into Seller-specific Invoices</td></tr><tr><td>Payment total differs</td><td>Check tax, shipping, discounts and first-party products</td></tr><tr><td>Commission differs</td><td>Review rates, postage commission and amendments</td></tr><tr><td>Refund total differs</td><td>Compare request, finalisation and payment dates</td></tr><tr><td>Seller payout differs from Sales</td><td>Deduct commission, fees, refunds and recoveries</td></tr><tr><td>Duplicate values appear</td><td>Confirm row grain and deduplicate Invoice-level fields</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Move from Transactional Reporting to Analytics":"<p>All Sales CSVs support investigation, control, reconciliation and ad hoc analysis. They are not automatically a complete analytical model.</p><p>Scalable analytics may require historical snapshots, consistent Seller and Category dimensions, refund restatement, first-party Sales, promotions, customer behaviour and external payment data.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>CSV extract</td><td>Ad hoc investigation and smaller recurring reports</td></tr><tr><td>Transactional API</td><td>Controlled custom extraction</td></tr><tr><td>Webhooks</td><td>Capturing changes as they occur</td></tr><tr><td>Snowflake Data Sharing</td><td>Scalable historical analytics</td></tr><tr><td>Performance Insights</td><td>Ready-to-use marketplace visibility</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Establish a Repeatable Reporting Process":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Define the business question</strong><p>State the decision the report must support.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Choose report and date field</strong><p>Use the source that matches the question.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Apply filters and columns</strong><p>Record the scope and exclusions.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Validate grain and identifiers</strong><p>Prevent duplicate Orders, Invoices or values.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Apply approved financial definitions</strong><p>Use documented tax, postage, discount and refund treatment.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Reconcile external totals</strong><p>Compare storefront, payment and accounting sources.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><div><strong>Publish with assumptions</strong><p>Retain the raw extract, logic and approval.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Reporting decision</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Purpose</td><td>Weekly marketplace Sales review</td></tr><tr><td>Source</td><td>All Sales CSV</td></tr><tr><td>Date field</td><td>Completed at</td></tr><tr><td>Grain</td><td>One record per distinct Invoice</td></tr><tr><td>Refund treatment</td><td>Refunds finalised in the period</td></tr><tr><td>First-party Sales</td><td>Excluded</td></tr><tr><td>Timezone</td><td>Marketplace timezone</td></tr><tr><td>Approver</td><td>Finance Manager</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Sales Reporting Permissions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Permission</th><th>Access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>View orders</td><td>All Sales, Not Dispatched and Awaiting Collection</td></tr><tr><td>Manage orders</td><td>Order actions and payout approval</td></tr><tr><td>View performance report</td><td>Performance Insights</td></tr><tr><td>View seller and sales summary reports</td><td>Sales Report and Seller Summary</td></tr><tr><td>View remittances report</td><td>Processed and unprocessed remittance records</td></tr><tr><td>View remittance summary report</td><td>Remittance history and downloads</td></tr><tr><td>View refund requests</td><td>Refund Requests and exports</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Apply least privilege because the reports can contain customer personal data, Seller financial information, payment IDs and commission arrangements.</p>","Test Sales Reporting":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>A test Order appears in All Sales</li><li>A multi-Seller Order creates the expected Seller Invoices</li><li>External IDs are searchable</li><li>Created, Completed and Paid dates are correct</li><li>Shipment date updates after fulfilment</li><li>Refund and Invoice Amendment values appear correctly</li><li>Remit after reflects the configured delay</li><li>Seller, Category, Brand, SKU and quantity fields are available</li><li>CSV export is delivered</li><li>Invoice-level totals are not double counted</li><li>Distinct Order and Invoice counts are correct</li><li>Storefront, payment and Marketplacer totals reconcile</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Reporting owners are named</li><li>Order, Invoice, Line Item and unit counts are understood</li><li>Approved Sales date and financial field are documented</li><li>Gross and net Sales definitions are agreed</li><li>Tax, postage, discount and refund treatment are agreed</li><li>First-party products are included or excluded intentionally</li><li>Seller and Category dimensions are maintained</li><li>External IDs are captured</li><li>CSV grain and double-count controls are validated</li><li>Marketplacer totals reconcile with storefront and payments</li><li>Remit after is not treated as proof of payment</li><li>Original extracts are retained</li><li>API or Snowflake access is planned where manual reporting will not scale</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360033163912-All-Sales-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">All Sales report</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14369744945933-Introduction-to-Marketplace-analytics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Introduction to Marketplace analytics</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14369804027661\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Access to data for Analysis</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator user role permissions</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["operator-dashboard","Operator Dashboard"],["seller-performance-reporting","Seller Performance Reporting"],["finance-reporting-operations","Finance Reporting"],["daily-operations","Daily Marketplace Operations"],["weekly-monthly-operations","Weekly and Monthly Operations"]]},"seller-performance-reporting":{"summary":"Set dispatch expectations, monitor marketplace-wide and Seller-specific service metrics, identify performance risks and turn dashboard results into clear Seller actions.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Seller management","Customer service","Commercial","Delivery","Technology"],"sections":{"Use the Seller Performance Dashboard":"<p>Go to <strong>Sellers → Seller Performance</strong>. Use the dashboard to configure dispatch expectations, review marketplace-wide service results, compare Sellers, identify risks and export detailed SLA data.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Set Seller expectations</strong><p>Configure the marketplace or Seller-specific dispatch SLA.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Monitor the metrics</strong><p>Review dispatch, cancellation, return and tracking performance.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Identify Sellers requiring review</strong><p>Use both percentages and absolute event volumes.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Investigate the underlying records</strong><p>Open Orders, Refund Requests, catalogue and integration evidence.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Agree corrective actions</strong><p>Record owners, targets and the next review period.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the dashboard to identify where investigation is required.</strong> Do not apply consequences from one percentage or rating without reviewing the transactions and business context.</div>","Configure the Dispatch SLA":"<p>Set the marketplace default under <strong>Sellers → Seller Performance → SLA Configuration</strong> or <strong>Configuration → Seller Settings</strong> using <strong>Days to fulfil order</strong>.</p><p>A Seller-specific value under <strong>Sellers → Manage Sellers → Edit Seller → Account Features</strong> overrides the marketplace default for that Seller.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Configuration</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace SLA</td><td>2 days</td></tr><tr><td>Seller-specific override</td><td>5 days</td></tr><tr><td>Effective SLA for that Seller</td><td>5 days</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use overrides for approved operating models such as made-to-order, bulky, personalised or regional fulfilment. Record the reason, approval, effective date and review date. Do not increase an SLA simply to hide poor performance.</p><p>SLA changes apply to new Orders only. Existing Orders retain the SLA that applied when they were created.</p>","Understand How the SLA Timer Works":"<p>The dispatch SLA begins from the Order payment date, and the payment day counts toward the SLA. Weekends are excluded.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Order paid Monday, 2-day SLA</td><td>Monday is day 1 and Tuesday is day 2; deadline is Tuesday 11:59 pm</td></tr><tr><td>Order paid Friday, 2-day SLA</td><td>Friday is day 1, weekend excluded, Monday is day 2</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The complete Order must be dispatched within the permitted period. One late Line Item causes the Order-level breach.</p><p>Fully cancelled Orders may be excluded from the dispatch breach calculation when all items are cancelled within the applicable early period. The cancellation still contributes to cancellation reporting.</p>","Select the Reporting Period":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Period</th><th>Best used for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Last 30 days</td><td>Current performance and recent corrective action</td></tr><tr><td>Last 90 days</td><td>More stable Seller comparison</td></tr><tr><td>Year to date</td><td>Longer-term commercial and governance reporting</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The selected period applies to marketplace metrics, the Seller table and exported data. Record the period whenever results are shared. A short period reacts quickly but can be volatile for low-volume Sellers.</p>","Read Marketplace-Wide Metrics":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Reporting grain</th><th>Core question</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dispatch SLA breach rate</td><td>Order level</td><td>Were all items dispatched within the effective SLA?</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation rate</td><td>Line Item quantity level</td><td>How much sold quantity was cancelled?</td></tr><tr><td>Return rate</td><td>Line Item quantity level</td><td>How much sold quantity was later refunded or returned?</td></tr><tr><td>Shipments without tracking</td><td>Shipment level</td><td>How often was tracking information missing?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>These percentages use different grains. Do not compare them as though they represent the same event type.</p>","Dispatch SLA Breach Rate":"<p>The marketplace dispatch SLA breach rate is the percentage of applicable Orders where the Seller did not dispatch every item within the effective SLA.</p><p>A rising rate may indicate inaccurate stock, warehouse capacity issues, missing Order ingestion, partial fulfilment, Seller process delay or a Shipment update that failed to synchronise.</p><p>Review the Seller table and the affected Orders before deciding on the cause.</p>","Return Rate":"<p>Return rate represents refunded or returned Line Item quantities as a percentage of quantities sold in the selected period.</p><p>Open the Refund Request to distinguish returnless refunds, physical returns, damaged items, incorrect items, lost parcels and change-of-mind outcomes.</p><p>Investigate product quality, descriptions, sizing, Variant mapping, fulfilment accuracy, packaging and Carrier performance rather than asking a Seller only to reduce the percentage.</p>","Cancellation Rate":"<p>Cancellation rate is calculated from cancelled Line Item quantities divided by quantities sold.</p><p>Separate Seller-controlled causes such as out of stock, fulfilment inability and product errors from customer-requested, fraud-control or integration-related cancellations.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cancellation type</th><th>Interpretation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller out of stock</td><td>Seller-controlled fulfilment issue</td></tr><tr><td>Product or price error</td><td>Catalogue governance issue</td></tr><tr><td>Customer changed mind</td><td>Customer behaviour</td></tr><tr><td>Fraud or compliance cancellation</td><td>Risk-control outcome</td></tr><tr><td>Integration-created duplicate</td><td>Technology issue</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Shipments Without Tracking":"<p>This metric shows the percentage of applicable Shipments without a tracking link. A Shipment using a Carrier configured without a tracking URL may be treated differently.</p><p>Investigate whether the Seller omitted tracking, the source system did not send it, Carrier mapping is incomplete, tracking was added after dispatch or the value was stored only in notes.</p><p>Missing tracking increases customer enquiries, delivery disputes and refund workload.</p>","Read Seller-Specific Metrics":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Column</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller</td><td>Seller account</td></tr><tr><td>Orders</td><td>Orders received in the selected period</td></tr><tr><td>Dispatch breaches</td><td>Orders missing the effective SLA</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation rate</td><td>Cancelled quantity percentage</td></tr><tr><td>Return rate</td><td>Returned or refunded quantity percentage</td></tr><tr><td>Without tracking links</td><td>Shipment tracking completeness</td></tr><tr><td>Current rating</td><td>Composite service summary</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use both the event count and percentage. A high-volume Seller can have a low rate but still affect many customers, while one event can produce a very high percentage for a new Seller.</p>","Understand the Seller Rating":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Rating component</th><th>Weight</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dispatch performance</td><td>30%</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation performance</td><td>30%</td></tr><tr><td>Return performance</td><td>30%</td></tr><tr><td>Tracking completeness</td><td>10%</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The Current Rating uses the preceding three months of performance and is recalculated weekly. Use it as a summary, not a replacement for the underlying metrics.</p><p>Two Sellers can have the same rating for different reasons. Apply the corrective action to the actual metric causing the result. The rating is visible to the Operator and the individual Seller, not as a public customer rating.</p>","Interpret New and Low-Volume Sellers":"<p>New Sellers can initially display limited or zero rating data while sufficient transactions are collected. A Seller with one breach across two Orders has a 50% rate, but the percentage is based on one affected customer Order.</p><p>Report the absolute event count, total Orders, time trading, repeat behaviour and customer impact. Define governance thresholds for new, low-volume, established and high-risk Sellers without changing the platform calculation.</p>","Investigate Dispatch Breaches":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Identify the Seller and period</strong><p>Record Orders, breach count and rate.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Confirm the effective SLA</strong><p>Check the marketplace default and Seller override.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Find affected Orders</strong><p>Compare payment and Shipment timestamps.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Review partial fulfilment and cancellations</strong><p>Confirm every Line Item outcome.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Check Seller and integration evidence</strong><p>Determine whether the issue is physical dispatch or data synchronisation.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Agree corrective action</strong><p>Set an owner, target and review date.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Root cause</th><th>Corrective action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Stock unavailable</td><td>Improve stock synchronisation and buffers</td></tr><tr><td>Seller dispatches late</td><td>Agree fulfilment improvement plan</td></tr><tr><td>Shipment not synchronised</td><td>Investigate integration</td></tr><tr><td>Partial Order remains open</td><td>Improve multi-Line Item fulfilment</td></tr><tr><td>Seller did not receive Order</td><td>Investigate notifications or Order integration</td></tr><tr><td>SLA is commercially unrealistic</td><td>Review the approved agreement</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Investigate Cancellation Rate":"<p>Review cancelled quantity, total quantity sold, reasons, initiator, affected products, stock history, Seller notes and integration logs.</p><p>Use reason-level reporting to distinguish preventable Seller failure from customer choice, marketplace risk control or a technology defect.</p>","Investigate Return Rate":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Return pattern</th><th>Investigation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Wrong size</td><td>Sizing data, charts and Variant options</td></tr><tr><td>Not as described</td><td>Product copy, images and specifications</td></tr><tr><td>Damaged in transit</td><td>Packaging and Carrier performance</td></tr><tr><td>Wrong item</td><td>Warehouse picking and SKU mapping</td></tr><tr><td>Faulty product</td><td>Product or supplier quality</td></tr><tr><td>Change of mind</td><td>Customer policy and Category behaviour</td></tr><tr><td>Lost parcel refund</td><td>Carrier and tracking process</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Review refund reasons, physical versus returnless outcomes, product, Variant, Category, customer evidence and repeat patterns.</p>","Investigate Missing Tracking":"<p>Review the Carrier, configured tracking URL, Shipment tracking number and link, Seller source data, MConnect or API mapping and timing of data entry.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Configure the Carrier tracking URL</li><li>Correct Seller Carrier mapping</li><li>Require tracking during dispatch</li><li>Update the integration payload</li><li>Stop storing tracking only in notes</li><li>Train Seller fulfilment users</li><li>Monitor the next reporting period</li></ul>","Export Seller Performance Data":"<p>Select the period, then use <strong>Export all data</strong>. The generated file can also be downloaded through <strong>Reporting → Imports & Exports</strong> using the file containing <code>sla_export</code>.</p><p>The export includes Seller ID, business name, Orders, dispatch breaches, cancellation and return values and rates, Shipments, missing tracking, rating and period dates.</p><p>Retain the raw CSV, selected period, extraction date, SLA configuration and Seller overrides. Create a separate working copy for analysis.</p>","Share Performance with Sellers":"<p>Sellers can review their own Sales and service results under <strong>Insights & Statistics → Performance Insights</strong>.</p><p>During a review, confirm the same period and SLA, explain the metric and grain, review specific examples, agree actions and record the next date.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Selected period</li><li>Total Orders</li><li>Number and rate of breaches</li><li>Cancelled and returned quantities with reasons</li><li>Missing tracking count</li><li>Specific Order examples</li><li>Required target and corrective action</li></ul>","Establish Performance Standards":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Decision required</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dispatch SLA</td><td>Permitted days</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation target</td><td>Acceptable rate and excluded reasons</td></tr><tr><td>Return target</td><td>Acceptable rate by Category or Seller type</td></tr><tr><td>Tracking target</td><td>Required completeness</td></tr><tr><td>Low-volume treatment</td><td>Minimum volume for formal action</td></tr><tr><td>Warning threshold</td><td>When the Seller receives notification</td></tr><tr><td>Remediation threshold</td><td>When an improvement plan is required</td></tr><tr><td>Escalation threshold</td><td>When commercial or compliance action begins</td></tr><tr><td>Recognition</td><td>How strong performance is acknowledged</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Category context matters. Fashion, bulky goods, perishables, made-to-order and regulated products may require different governance interpretation.</p>","Run Seller Performance Reviews":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cadence</th><th>Focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Weekly</td><td>New breaches, overdue Orders, cancellations, tracking and active remediation</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly</td><td>30-day metrics, prior-period comparison, root causes and actions</td></tr><tr><td>Quarterly</td><td>90-day and year-to-date trends, commercial impact and Seller suitability</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use a scorecard with current result, previous result, target, status, action and owner. Include metric definitions and the selected period.</p>","Manage Underperformance":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Level</th><th>Use when</th><th>Response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1. Clarification</td><td>Isolated issue, low volume or data uncertainty</td><td>Review examples and correct process or data</td></tr><tr><td>2. Performance warning</td><td>Target missed or repeated customer impact</td><td>Provide written metrics and improvement target</td></tr><tr><td>3. Corrective action plan</td><td>Repeated breaches and missed commitments</td><td>Set actions, owners, deadlines and consequences</td></tr><tr><td>4. Commercial or operational restriction</td><td>Material continued failure</td><td>Apply approved payment, catalogue, trading or suspension controls</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Do not apply restrictions without contractual basis and approval. Recognise strong dispatch, low preventable cancellation, appropriate returns, complete tracking and sustained improvement.</p>","Understand Data Freshness and Limitations":"<p>Seller Performance is not a real-time incident monitor. Dashboard metrics refresh on a schedule and the Current Rating refreshes weekly.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Use</th><th>Source</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Immediate fulfilment follow-up</td><td>Orders → Not Dispatched</td></tr><tr><td>Transaction investigation</td><td>Orders → All Sales</td></tr><tr><td>Live refund workflow</td><td>Orders → Refund Requests</td></tr><tr><td>Trend and SLA reporting</td><td>Sellers → Seller Performance</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The dashboard does not independently explain cancellation cause, physical versus returnless refunds, Carrier configuration, integration failures or low-volume volatility. Open the underlying records.</p>","Test Seller Performance Reporting":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Marketplace and Seller-specific SLAs can be configured</li><li>SLA changes affect new Orders only</li><li>Payment date and weekend treatment behave as expected</li><li>Partial dispatch causes an Order-level breach</li><li>Cancellation and return quantities contribute correctly</li><li>Missing tracking behaves according to Carrier configuration</li><li>30-day, 90-day and year-to-date periods work</li><li>The Seller table sorts correctly</li><li>Rating refresh timing is understood</li><li>The CSV export uses the selected period</li><li>Sellers can view their own Performance Insights</li><li>Operator roles have the intended access</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The marketplace dispatch SLA is approved</li><li>Seller-specific exceptions are documented</li><li>Sellers understand complete-Order dispatch expectations</li><li>SLA timing and weekend treatment are understood</li><li>Order-level and Line Item-level metrics are distinguished</li><li>Cancellation reasons are reviewed before Seller attribution</li><li>Returnless and physical returns are distinguished</li><li>Carrier tracking configuration is validated</li><li>Low-volume and new Seller treatment is documented</li><li>Weekly, monthly and quarterly reviews are established</li><li>Warning and escalation thresholds are approved</li><li>Corrective-action templates are ready</li><li>Raw exports are retained</li><li>Sellers receive the period and examples</li><li>Data freshness is understood</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599850695821-Intro-to-the-Seller-Performance-dashboard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Intro to the Seller Performance dashboard</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570670327437-Configure-Seller-Performance-SLAs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure Seller Performance SLAs</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570962112397-Marketplace-metrics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplace metrics</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25571003783309-Seller-metrics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller metrics</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599997635341-Export-SLA-seller-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Export SLA seller data</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/36711915681933-Seller-performance-insights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller performance insights</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["operator-dashboard","Operator Dashboard"],["sales-reporting","Sales Reporting"],["seller-account-creation","Seller Account Creation"],["daily-operations","Daily Marketplace Operations"],["weekly-monthly-operations","Weekly and Monthly Operations"]]},"catalogue-reporting":{"summary":"Build a clear view of catalogue health by monitoring Product Vetting, rejections, Catalog Rule failures, mapping, product status, stock and Seller-specific quality issues.","audience":["Catalogue operations","Marketplace operations","Seller management","Commercial","Technology","Integrations"],"sections":{"Understand Catalogue Reporting":"<p>Catalogue reporting is assembled from several operational views rather than one catalogue dashboard.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>What it shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Adverts → Product Vetting</td><td>Products awaiting approval, rejected products and rule outcomes</td></tr><tr><td>Adverts → Search Adverts</td><td>Marketplace-wide filters for Seller, Category, Brand, status, stock, dates and quality</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Portal → Products → Mapping</td><td>Source values awaiting Category, Brand or Option Value mapping</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Portal → Manage Products</td><td>Rule errors, invalid Variants and Seller-side product data</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect workspace</td><td>Imports, source data, synchronisation and errors</td></tr><tr><td>Reporting → Imports & Exports</td><td>Product exports and bulk-processing files</td></tr><tr><td>Customer-facing storefront</td><td>Final published catalogue experience</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller product source</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Import or product creation</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Mapping</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Catalog Rule validation</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Product Vetting</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Publication and stock</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Connected storefront</div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>A healthy catalogue is not simply a large catalogue.</strong> Products must be mapped, valid, approved where required, published, stocked and visible through the intended storefront.</div>","Build the Core Catalogue Queues":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Queue</th><th>Operational question</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Awaiting vetting</td><td>Which products require Operator approval?</td></tr><tr><td>Rejected</td><td>Which products were returned for correction?</td></tr><tr><td>Recently updated</td><td>Which approved products changed after going live?</td></tr><tr><td>Failed Catalog Rules</td><td>Which products fail automated requirements?</td></tr><tr><td>Unmapped</td><td>Which Seller source values are not aligned?</td></tr><tr><td>Invalid</td><td>Which products or Variants contain missing or incompatible information?</td></tr><tr><td>Not published</td><td>Which valid products are not currently published?</td></tr><tr><td>No stock</td><td>Which products are unavailable?</td></tr><tr><td>Integration errors</td><td>Which products are delayed or wrong because synchronisation failed?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Do not combine these conditions into one generic offline-products queue. Each has a different owner and corrective action.</p>","Product Vetting Queue":"<p>Go to <strong>Adverts → Product Vetting</strong>. Search by Product ID, name, SKU or barcode and filter by Seller, Brand, Category, stock, previous rejection and Catalog Rule errors.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Correct Seller, Category and Brand</li><li>Clear title and description</li><li>Required attributes and suitable images</li><li>Valid Variants and option combinations</li><li>Pricing, shipping and tax data</li><li>Catalog Rule and policy compliance</li></ul><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Products awaiting vetting</td><td>Current workload</td></tr><tr><td>Oldest submission age</td><td>Launch-delay risk</td></tr><tr><td>Average review time</td><td>Catalogue service level</td></tr><tr><td>Approved products</td><td>Throughput</td></tr><tr><td>Rejected products</td><td>Quality outcome</td></tr><tr><td>Approval rate</td><td>Submission quality</td></tr><tr><td>Queue by Seller or Category</td><td>Workload concentration</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Prioritise launch blockers, campaign products, resubmissions and ageing work. Approval begins asynchronous publication processing.</p>","Rejected Products":"<p>Use the Rejected tab or Previously rejected filter. An actionable rejection reason explains what is wrong, where it appears, what must change, the required standard and the correct source system.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Weak</th><th>Actionable</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Description issue</td><td>The description does not include material or dimensions. Update both fields in Shopify, allow the next sync and resubmit.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Track rejection reason, Seller, Category, date, resubmission, repeated rejection count, correction time and final outcome. Bulk reject only when the exact same issue and correction apply to every selected product.</p>","Recently Updated Products":"<p>Approved product and Variant changes do not automatically re-enter pre-publication vetting. Enable <strong>Notify of advert changes</strong> under <strong>Configuration → Advert Settings</strong> and select the attributes that require monitoring.</p><p>The Recently updated tab can show the field, old value and new value for monitored changes such as title, description, images, Category, Brand, price, Sale price, options, SKU, barcode, shipping profile and tax.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Operator action</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Approve</td><td>Product remains live and leaves the queue</td></tr><tr><td>Reject</td><td>Product is unpublished and returned to the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Message Seller</td><td>Product can remain live while a safe correction is made</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Recently updated is a monitoring queue, not a second pre-publication approval queue.</strong> The changes are already live when they appear.</div>","Failed Catalog Rules":"<p>Catalog Rules validate products before vetting or publication. Use Product Vetting filters or <strong>Adverts → Search Adverts → With Failed Catalog Rules?</strong>.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Outcome</th><th>Product already online</th><th>Product offline</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Warning</td><td>Remains online but displays the error</td><td>Cannot progress until corrected</td></tr><tr><td>Unpublish</td><td>Is taken offline</td><td>Cannot progress until corrected</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Track failures by rule, Seller and Category, warning versus unpublish outcome, correction time and products taken offline. Creating or changing a rule triggers background validation, so results may not update immediately.</p><p>A high failure count can indicate poor Seller data, unclear standards, unsupported source fields or an incorrect rule. Investigate the rule as well as the product.</p>","Unmapped Products":"<p>Mapping translates Seller source values into marketplace Categories, Brands and Option Values. Go to <strong>Seller Portal → Products → Mapping</strong> and review each tab.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Unmapped Category values</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>Unmapped Brand values</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>Unmapped Option Values</td><td>28</td></tr><tr><td>Products affected</td><td>450</td></tr><tr><td>Oldest pending mapping</td><td>6 days</td></tr><tr><td>Seller launch blocked</td><td>Yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>One unmapped source value can affect hundreds of products. Auto-mapping can assist new source values, but recommendations and lower-confidence results still require review.</p><p>Where no suitable target exists, confirm the Seller value, search for an equivalent, obtain taxonomy approval, create the new marketplace value only when justified and then validate the affected products.</p>","Product Status and Displayability":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Online</td><td>Live for customers to view and purchase</td></tr><tr><td>Not Published</td><td>Not currently published</td></tr><tr><td>Invalid</td><td>Required information is missing or incompatible</td></tr><tr><td>Not Displayed, No Stock</td><td>Unavailable because relevant stock is zero</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Mapped correctly</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Passes validation</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Approved where required</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Product and Variant published</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Stock available</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Storefront synchronisation successful</div></div><p>Status is only one layer of visibility. When a product is missing from the storefront, check product status, Variant status, stock, mapping, rules, vetting, publication processing and front-end integration.</p>","Stock Issues":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Condition</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>In stock</td><td>At least one relevant Variant is available</td><td>No stock action</td></tr><tr><td>Low stock</td><td>At or below the configured threshold</td><td>Seller replenishment or source review</td></tr><tr><td>No stock</td><td>No purchasable quantity remains</td><td>Confirm whether expected</td></tr><tr><td>Unexpected zero stock</td><td>Source has stock but Marketplacer does not</td><td>Investigate synchronisation</td></tr><tr><td>Stale positive stock</td><td>Marketplacer has stock but source does not</td><td>Stop oversell risk</td></tr><tr><td>No-stock product awaiting vetting</td><td>Valid but unavailable</td><td>Review quality separately from availability</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Configure the limited stock threshold under <strong>Configuration → Product Settings → Advert Settings</strong>. For integrated Sellers, compare source stock, payload, Marketplacer Variant stock and storefront availability.</p><p>Consider stock buffers, excluded zero-stock imports, inactive-product behaviour and failed scheduled synchronisation when interpreting the report.</p>","Product and Variant Errors":"<p>A product can be mapped but still invalid. Common product errors include missing titles, descriptions, images, Category, Brand, required attributes, price, tax or rule compliance. Variant errors include missing or duplicate SKU and barcode, invalid option combinations, price, stock, shipping profile or required Variant attributes.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Open the product</strong><p>Identify the visible error and affected Variant.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Classify the issue</strong><p>Product, Variant, mapping, rule, stock or integration.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Confirm the source of truth</strong><p>Determine which system owns the field.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Correct the source</strong><p>Avoid changes that will be overwritten.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Allow import and validation</strong><p>Wait for the approved process to rerun.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Confirm Marketplacer and storefront</strong><p>Validate status, stock and customer visibility.</p></div></div></div>","Catalogue Coverage and Assortment":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Total products</td><td>Distinct Advert IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Total Variants</td><td>Distinct Variant IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Online products</td><td>Products currently Online</td></tr><tr><td>Live stocked products</td><td>Online products with at least one in-stock Variant</td></tr><tr><td>Invalid products</td><td>Products with unresolved validation</td></tr><tr><td>Failed-rule products</td><td>Products failing one or more rules</td></tr><tr><td>Awaiting-vetting products</td><td>Products requiring Operator approval</td></tr><tr><td>Category coverage</td><td>Categories with at least one live stocked product</td></tr><tr><td>Seller contribution</td><td>Live products or Variants supplied by each Seller</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Report the funnel from imported to mapped, valid, approved, Online, stocked and storefront-visible. Product count and Variant count are different.</p><p>Use the stage where products are lost to determine whether the issue is mapping, validation, publication or stock.</p>","Seller and Category Quality":"<p>Create Seller scorecards using both volume and quality. A catalogue-ready product is mapped, valid, approved where required, published and stocked.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Question</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Catalogue-ready rate</td><td>What share of the agreed Seller scope is usable?</td></tr><tr><td>Failed rules</td><td>Which automated standards are missed?</td></tr><tr><td>Rejections</td><td>Which human-review standards are missed?</td></tr><tr><td>No-stock products</td><td>Is assortment available to buy?</td></tr><tr><td>Correction time</td><td>How quickly does the Seller resolve feedback?</td></tr><tr><td>Category concentration</td><td>Where are quality issues clustered?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use Category-level results to improve taxonomy, Prototypes, Option Types, Catalog Rules, onboarding guidance and source-system mappings.</p>","Export and Analyse Catalogue Data":"<p>Apply filters in <strong>Adverts → Search Adverts</strong>, export the result, retain the raw file and create a separate working copy.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Record environment, extraction time and filters</li><li>Confirm whether rows represent products or Variants</li><li>Retain Advert, Variant, Seller, Category, Brand and External IDs</li><li>Keep dated snapshots for trend reporting</li><li>Do not overwrite the raw extract</li></ul><p>Dated extracts allow the Operator to measure catalogue growth, products moving Online or offline, stock recovery, correction rates and Category coverage over time.</p>","Correct Issues at the Right Source":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Product source</th><th>Preferred correction point</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Portal manual product</td><td>Seller Portal</td></tr><tr><td>Bulk spreadsheet</td><td>Approved bulk workbook or Seller Portal</td></tr><tr><td>Shopify through MConnect</td><td>Shopify unless the field is excluded from sync</td></tr><tr><td>Other ecommerce integration</td><td>Seller’s connected platform</td></tr><tr><td>Seller API</td><td>Seller integration</td></tr><tr><td>Operator taxonomy</td><td>Operator Portal</td></tr><tr><td>Catalog Rule</td><td>Operator Portal</td></tr><tr><td>Storefront merchandising</td><td>Ecommerce platform or front end</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Manual Marketplacer changes can be overwritten by the integrated source. Correct Marketplacer directly only when it is the approved source or an authorised exception has been documented.</p>","Catalogue Operating Rhythm":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cadence</th><th>Review</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Daily</td><td>Vetting, rejections, rule failures, unmapped values, invalid products, integration errors, unexpected no stock and high-risk live changes</td></tr><tr><td>Weekly</td><td>Queue ageing, approval and rejection trends, mapping backlog, catalogue-ready rate, Category gaps and recurring stock issues</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly</td><td>Catalogue growth, Seller quality, rule effectiveness, Brand duplication, inactive products and assortment health</td></tr><tr><td>Quarterly</td><td>Taxonomy, governance, trusted Seller exceptions, source of truth, enrichment and duplicate-product strategy</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Investigate Common Exceptions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Exception</th><th>What to review</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Approved but not visible</td><td>Publication processing, stock, Variant publication, mapping and storefront sync</td></tr><tr><td>Remains in vetting after correction</td><td>Unresolved rule, Variant or required field</td></tr><tr><td>Flag remains after rule change</td><td>Background revalidation</td></tr><tr><td>Wrong Category</td><td>Source mapping and saved target</td></tr><tr><td>Stock in source but zero in Marketplacer</td><td>Integration, buffer, Variant match and sync time</td></tr><tr><td>Manual correction disappears</td><td>Integrated source overwrote the value</td></tr><tr><td>Product count differs</td><td>Product versus Variant grain and filters</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Assign corrective action to the responsible owner. Do not repeatedly ask a Seller to fix a platform configuration or taxonomy issue.</p>","Catalogue Reporting Permissions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Permission</th><th>Access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Manage product catalog</td><td>Search, export, import, approve and reject products</td></tr><tr><td>View catalog rules</td><td>View marketplace Catalog Rules</td></tr><tr><td>Manage catalog rules</td><td>Create, update and delete rules</td></tr><tr><td>Login as retailer</td><td>Access the Seller Portal as the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Manage categories</td><td>Manage taxonomy</td></tr><tr><td>Manage brands</td><td>Create, update and merge Brands</td></tr><tr><td>Manage prototypes</td><td>Manage Prototypes</td></tr><tr><td>Manage option types</td><td>Manage Option Types and Values</td></tr><tr><td>View imports and exports</td><td>Access marketplace files</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Apply least privilege. A reporting user may not need permission to delete products, change taxonomy or create rules.</p>","Test Catalogue Reporting":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>A new product appears in Product Vetting</li><li>Approval, rejection and resubmission work</li><li>Failed-rule filters and Warning or Unpublish outcomes work</li><li>Mapping can be completed for Category, Brand and Option Values</li><li>An invalid Variant is visible</li><li>Online, Not Published, Invalid and no-stock conditions can be identified</li><li>Low-stock behaviour is correct</li><li>A monitored live change appears in Recently updated</li><li>Search Adverts exports the intended result set</li><li>Product and Variant counts are calculated correctly</li><li>Marketplacer and storefront visibility reconcile</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Every catalogue queue has an owner</li><li>Product Vetting standards and response times are documented</li><li>Rejection reasons are actionable</li><li>Recently updated monitoring is configured</li><li>Catalog Rule outcomes and processing delays are understood</li><li>Mapping ownership and new-value approval are documented</li><li>Product, Variant and stocked-assortment counts are distinguished</li><li>Low-stock configuration is confirmed</li><li>Source-of-truth ownership is documented</li><li>Manual edits are protected from overwrite</li><li>Seller and Category scorecards use agreed definitions</li><li>Raw exports and reporting filters are retained</li><li>Marketplacer products reconcile with the storefront</li><li>Daily, weekly and monthly catalogue reviews are established</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39514847581709-Search-Adverts-in-the-Operator-portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Search Adverts in the Operator Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741316387725-Review-and-approve-products-adverts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and approve products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27467503428237-Reviewing-vetted-and-approved-products-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Reviewing vetted and approved products and Variants</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/19655643593101-Catalog-rules\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Catalog Rules</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/34049716990861-Filtering-products-with-catalog-rule-errors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Filtering products with Catalog Rule errors</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003511551-Map-product-categories-brands-features-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Map product Categories, Brands, features and Variants</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360007518911-Set-limited-stock-threshold\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Set limited stock threshold</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["product-vetting","Product Vetting"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"],["mapping","Mapping"],["catalogue-quality","Catalogue Quality Operations"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"]]},"finance-reporting-operations":{"summary":"Reconcile marketplace sales, commission, merchant fees, refunds, Seller remittances and external payments using consistent definitions, dates and transaction identifiers.","audience":["Finance","Marketplace operations","Commercial","Customer service","Seller management","Technology","Integrations"],"sections":{"Choose the Right Finance View":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Best used for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Performance Insights</td><td>Headline Sales, commission and trends</td></tr><tr><td>Orders → All Sales</td><td>Transaction-level fees, refunds and remittance investigation</td></tr><tr><td>Reporting → Remittances</td><td>Processed and unprocessed Seller payment records</td></tr><tr><td>Orders → Refund Requests</td><td>Refund workflow and remittance effect</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Invoices and Amendments</td><td>Original transaction and later correction</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Invoices and credit notes</td><td>Operator charges and reversals</td></tr><tr><td>Payment gateway</td><td>Customer payment and actual refund</td></tr><tr><td>Payout system or bank</td><td>Actual Seller transfer</td></tr><tr><td>Accounting platform</td><td>Ledger and tax reconciliation</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the report that matches the financial question.</strong> Marketplacer is not the marketplace’s complete bank or accounting ledger.</div>","Define the Finance Measures":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Recommended definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Total Order Value or GMV</td><td>Gross included Seller Invoice value before later refunds</td></tr><tr><td>Customer Paid</td><td>Amount collected through the payment transaction</td></tr><tr><td>Gross commission</td><td>Commission originally charged</td></tr><tr><td>Net commission</td><td>Gross commission less reversals</td></tr><tr><td>Merchant fees</td><td>Fixed and percentage fees charged to Sellers</td></tr><tr><td>Seller remittance</td><td>Amount payable after commission, fees, tax, refunds and adjustments</td></tr><tr><td>Customer refund</td><td>Amount actually returned through the payment method</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance recovery</td><td>Amount removed from the Seller payable position</td></tr><tr><td>Processed remittance</td><td>Eligible Remittance Advice due for payment</td></tr><tr><td>Actual Seller payout</td><td>Funds transferred through the payout provider</td></tr><tr><td>Seller balance</td><td>Net positive or negative payable position</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Document tax, postage, discounts, refund treatment, date field, transaction grain, first-party scope and currency for every recurring measure.</p>","GMV and Total Order Value":"<p>Performance Insights labels the headline gross metric <strong>Total order value</strong>. Treat it as a gross transaction measure, not Operator revenue and not net Sales.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Total customer Invoice value</td><td>$1,000</td></tr><tr><td>Operator commission</td><td>$150</td></tr><tr><td>Merchant fees</td><td>$20</td></tr><tr><td>Seller remittance before later refunds</td><td>$830</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>If $200 is later refunded, the original gross value remains $1,000 while the defined net Sales measure may be $800. Use refunds and Invoice Amendments for the net view.</p><p>Document whether GMV includes marketplace Sellers only, first-party products, tax, postage, discounts, incomplete Orders and multiple currencies.</p>","Commission":"<p>Report gross commission, commission returned to the Seller, commission tax, commission on postage and net commission separately.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Performance Insights</td><td>Headline commission and trends</td></tr><tr><td>All Sales</td><td>Transaction-level commission, tax, Seller, product and Category</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Invoice</td><td>Commission and merchant-fee detail charged to the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Commission credit note</td><td>Refund-related commission reversal</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Historical commission must use the rate stored on the original transaction, not only the Seller’s current Commission Package. Investigate package, Category, postage commission, tax, promotions, refunds and credit notes when values differ.</p>","Merchant Fees":"<p>Merchant fees can be fixed, percentage-based or a combination, with payment-gateway-specific overrides. They affect Seller remittance, not the customer-facing price.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example component</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Order value</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Percentage fee</td><td>1%</td></tr><tr><td>Fixed fee</td><td>$0.50</td></tr><tr><td>Total merchant fee</td><td>$1.50</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Separate merchant fees charged, fees returned, fees retained, net merchant-fee revenue and the payment provider’s actual processing cost. For partial refunds, review the remaining Invoice, gateway behaviour and Seller agreement before reversing a fee.</p>","Remittances":"<p>A remittance is the net marketplace amount payable to a Seller after the approved deductions and adjustments.</p><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller-funded item and postage value</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Less commission, merchant fees and withheld tax</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Less refund recoveries</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Plus or minus approved adjustments</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller remittance</div></div><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller Invoice is complete</li><li>Payment release is approved or automatic</li><li>Remittance delay has passed</li><li>Seller schedule is due</li><li>Eligible Seller total is positive</li></ul><p>Marketplacer evaluates eligibility through the remittance process. A record that does not pass remains available for a later cycle.</p>","View Processed and Unprocessed Remittances":"<p>Go to <strong>Reporting → Remittances</strong>. The current report separates Processed Remittance Advices from Unprocessed Remittances.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>View</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Processed Remittance Advices</td><td>Eligible net positive records included in an advice</td></tr><tr><td>Unprocessed Remittances</td><td>Invoices or amendments still failing one or more checks</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Pending reason</th><th>Operator response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>No payment details</td><td>Work with the Seller to complete payout details</td></tr><tr><td>Payment not released</td><td>Follow the approval process</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance delay not passed</td><td>Continue monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Non-positive Seller total</td><td>Wait for future eligible Sales or apply recovery policy</td></tr><tr><td>System error</td><td>Investigate and escalate</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice incomplete</td><td>Resolve every Line Item</td></tr><tr><td>Seller schedule not due</td><td>Wait for the next cycle</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Processed does not always mean paid into the Seller’s bank account.</strong> Reconcile the Remittance Advice with the payout provider or bank.</div>","Refunds and Invoice Amendments":"<p>The original Seller Invoice records the Sale. A completed cancellation or return creates an <strong>Invoice Amendment</strong> that records the later financial change.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Refund field</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Requested refund amount</td><td>Amount originally requested</td></tr><tr><td>Amount refunded cash</td><td>Customer cash amount recorded for the completed refund</td></tr><tr><td>Refund date</td><td>Date finalised in Marketplacer</td></tr><tr><td>Remitted amount</td><td>Seller amount included in remittance</td></tr><tr><td>Quantity returned</td><td>Affected quantity</td></tr><tr><td>Payment gateway and transaction ID</td><td>Customer payment reference</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The requested amount, customer cash refund and Seller remittance amount can differ. Reconcile all three. Where enabled, Marketplacer also creates Seller and commission credit notes.</p>","Seller Balances":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Positive</td><td>Eligible Sales +$500, refund recoveries -$120, net +$380</td></tr><tr><td>Negative</td><td>Eligible Sales +$100, refund recoveries -$180, net -$80</td></tr><tr><td>Becomes positive later</td><td>Existing -$80 plus new eligible Sales +$150 gives +$70</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>No Remittance Advice is created while the eligible total is zero or negative. Future positive Sales offset the recovery.</p><p>If the Seller already received the original Invoice payment, the refund recovery reduces later payable activity through the Invoice Amendment. Monitor Sellers with no future Sales, repeated refunds, suspension or offboarding and define external recovery or write-off authority.</p>","Finance Dates and Reporting Periods":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>What it represents</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Created at</td><td>Order record created</td></tr><tr><td>Completed at</td><td>Customer Order completed</td></tr><tr><td>Paid at</td><td>Customer payment completed</td></tr><tr><td>Shipment date</td><td>Seller dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Remit after</td><td>Delay passed</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Advice date</td><td>Advice generated</td></tr><tr><td>Recorded payout date</td><td>Seller payment recorded</td></tr><tr><td>Refund Request date</td><td>Refund workflow created</td></tr><tr><td>Refund date</td><td>Marketplacer refund finalised</td></tr><tr><td>Payment-provider refund date</td><td>Customer money returned</td></tr><tr><td>Credit-note date</td><td>Credit note generated</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use the date that matches the event being reported. Record marketplace timezone and complete-period rules when reconciling systems using different time zones.</p>","Finance Documents":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Invoice</td><td>Customer transaction for one Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Invoice</td><td>Commission and merchant fees charged by the Operator</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice Amendment</td><td>Later refund or financial correction</td></tr><tr><td>Seller credit note</td><td>Refund against the Seller Invoice</td></tr><tr><td>Commission credit note</td><td>Commission correction</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Advice</td><td>Net amount due to the Seller</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>When immutable financial PDFs are enabled, later refunds do not rewrite original documents. Separate amendments and credit notes preserve the audit history.</p>","Reconcile the Complete Transaction":"<div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Storefront Order</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Marketplacer Order and Seller Invoice</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Customer payment transaction</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Commission and merchant fees</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Refund and Invoice Amendment</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Remittance Advice</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller payout</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Accounting ledger</div></div><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Confirm period and timezone</strong><p>Use one approved reporting basis.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Extract transaction data</strong><p>Retain raw Marketplacer and external files.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Validate grain and identifiers</strong><p>Match Order, Invoice and Line Item correctly.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Match payments and refunds</strong><p>Confirm actual customer money movement.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Calculate Seller position</strong><p>Apply fees, tax and amendments.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Match Remittance Advices to payouts</strong><p>Confirm actual Seller transfer.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><div><strong>Match the accounting ledger</strong><p>Record and resolve remaining exceptions.</p></div></div></div><p>Retain Marketplacer Order, Invoice and Line Item IDs, external IDs, payment transaction, Refund Request, Invoice Amendment, Remittance Advice, payout and accounting references.</p>","Monitor Finance Exceptions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Exception</th><th>Primary owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer paid but Marketplacer Order incomplete</td><td>Payments and Technology</td></tr><tr><td>Order complete but payment missing</td><td>Payments and Technology</td></tr><tr><td>Commission differs from expected</td><td>Finance and Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Invoice not released</td><td>Finance or Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Seller balance zero or negative</td><td>Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Processed Advice not paid</td><td>Finance or payout team</td></tr><tr><td>Refund finalised but customer payment failed</td><td>Finance or Customer Service</td></tr><tr><td>Customer refunded but amendment missing</td><td>Finance and Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Tax differs between systems</td><td>Finance and Technology</td></tr><tr><td>Unknown calculation error</td><td>Marketplacer Support</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Review urgent payment and refund failures daily, aged remittances and negative balances weekly, and gross or net revenue, Seller liability, payouts, credit notes and ledger differences monthly.</p>","Export and Retain an Audit Trail":"<p>Store raw evidence, working reconciliation and approved output separately.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Layer</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Raw evidence</td><td>All Sales, refunds, remittance, payment, payout and accounting extracts; financial PDFs</td></tr><tr><td>Working reconciliation</td><td>Period, timezone, source files, filters, formulas, matches and investigation notes</td></tr><tr><td>Approved output</td><td>Final report, Finance approval, unresolved exceptions and correction entries</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Do not overwrite raw extracts, remove identifiers before reconciliation, mix Sandbox and Production or change source totals without an adjustment log.</p>","Finance Reporting Permissions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Permission</th><th>Access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>View orders</td><td>All Sales and available financial documents</td></tr><tr><td>Manage orders</td><td>Payout approval and Order actions</td></tr><tr><td>View refund requests</td><td>Refund reporting</td></tr><tr><td>Process refunds</td><td>Financial finalisation</td></tr><tr><td>View performance report</td><td>Performance Insights</td></tr><tr><td>View remittances report</td><td>Processed and unprocessed remittance records</td></tr><tr><td>View remittance summary report</td><td>History and downloads</td></tr><tr><td>Rerun remittance job manually</td><td>Manual remittance processing</td></tr><tr><td>Manage commissions</td><td>Commission Packages and rules</td></tr><tr><td>Manage marketplace configuration</td><td>Finance, Seller and payment settings</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Separate investigation access from permission to approve payouts, process refunds, change commercial configuration or rerun financial jobs.</p>","Test Finance Reporting":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Completed Orders appear in the expected reporting period</li><li>Total order value matches the relevant Invoices and remains gross after refunds</li><li>Commission and tax fields are correct</li><li>Commission on postage behaves as configured</li><li>Merchant fees and gateway overrides calculate correctly</li><li>Commission Invoice values match the Order</li><li>Seller remittance calculation is correct</li><li>Incomplete, unreleased or delayed Invoices remain unprocessed</li><li>Positive and negative Seller balances behave correctly</li><li>Processed remittance export matches the Portal</li><li>A refund creates the correct Invoice Amendment and credit notes</li><li>The customer refund executes once</li><li>Seller payout matches the Remittance Advice</li><li>The accounting system records the expected values</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>GMV or Total Order Value is defined</li><li>Gross and net Sales are separate</li><li>Operator revenue is not confused with customer value</li><li>Commission and merchant-fee ownership is assigned</li><li>Commission on postage and refund treatment are documented</li><li>Remittance delay, schedule and release ownership are approved</li><li>Finance understands that an Advice is not proof of bank payment</li><li>Actual Seller payouts are reconciled</li><li>Negative balance handling is documented</li><li>Requested refund, cash refund and Seller recovery are distinguished</li><li>Invoice Amendments and credit notes are configured intentionally</li><li>Dates, timezone and identifiers are documented</li><li>Raw extracts are preserved</li><li>Daily, weekly and monthly reconciliation is defined</li><li>Finance permissions support separation of duties</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16037162615949\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Performance Insights</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360033163912-All-Sales-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">All Sales report</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16214118514189-View-remittance-summary-as-an-operator-implementation-2-0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View remittance summary as an Operator</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038673291-Remittance-Calculation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Calculating remittance on Orders</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31442688192269-Refunds-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Refunds Report</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925550144269-Credit-notes-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Credit Notes Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360055605531-Setting-Merchant-Fees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Setting Merchant Fees</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["sales-reporting","Sales Reporting"],["refund-financial-adjustments","Refund Financial Adjustments"],["remittances","Remittances"],["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["merchant-fees","Merchant Fees"]]},"daily-operations":{"summary":"Run a controlled daily operating routine across Orders, fulfilment, refunds, catalogue, integrations, Seller communications and customer escalations so issues are identified, owned and resolved before they become larger marketplace risks.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Customer service","Seller management","Catalogue","Finance","Technology","Integrations"],"sections":{"Establish the Daily Operating Rhythm":"<p>Daily marketplace operations protect customer experience, Seller service levels, catalogue availability, fulfilment, refunds, payouts, integration continuity and financial accuracy.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Check marketplace health</strong><p>Review status, incidents and integration alerts.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Review customer-critical work</strong><p>Prioritise Orders, payments, fulfilment and refunds.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Review Seller work</strong><p>Follow up late dispatch and Seller questions.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Review catalogue queues</strong><p>Process launch blockers and quality issues.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Review finance-critical actions</strong><p>Apply payout and refund controls.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Record ownership and handover</strong><p>Assign unresolved work with deadlines.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>A queue is not managed simply because it has been opened.</strong> Every material item must be resolved, assigned or deliberately monitored.</div>","Start with Platform Health":"<p>Begin with Marketplacer system status, Dashboard Problem Reports, integration alerts, storefront availability, checkout and payment health and unresolved incidents.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scope</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Platform-wide</td><td>Marketplacer service degradation</td></tr><tr><td>Operator-wide</td><td>Storefront, payment or middleware failure</td></tr><tr><td>Seller-specific</td><td>One Seller MConnect connection disabled</td></tr><tr><td>Transaction-specific</td><td>One Order, product or webhook failed</td></tr><tr><td>User-specific</td><td>Access or permission issue</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>When an incident is active, confirm scope, stop risky retries, identify affected records, assign an owner, apply a safe fallback and reconcile the backlog after recovery.</p>","Orders Requiring Action":"<p>Review the Dashboard, <strong>Orders → Not Dispatched</strong>, <strong>Awaiting Collection</strong> where applicable, <strong>All Sales</strong> and integration exception queues.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Newly paid Orders</li><li>Orders missing from Marketplacer</li><li>Seller Invoices not delivered to the Seller</li><li>Undispatched and partially dispatched Line Items</li><li>Missing Carrier or tracking</li><li>Duplicate Orders</li><li>Payment and Order status mismatches</li><li>Customer delivery escalations</li></ul><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Customer Order</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller Invoice</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Affected Line Item and quantity</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Shipment, cancellation or refund record</div></div><p>Record Marketplacer and external identifiers so every team investigates the same transaction.</p>","Late Dispatch":"<p>Review <strong>Orders → Not Dispatched</strong> every operating day. Compare payment date, effective SLA, current date, weekend treatment, dispatched and cancelled quantities.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Daily action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Within SLA</td><td>Monitor</td></tr><tr><td>Approaching SLA</td><td>Proactive reminder</td></tr><tr><td>SLA breached</td><td>Formal Seller follow-up</td></tr><tr><td>Cannot fulfil</td><td>Cancellation required</td></tr><tr><td>Physically sent but not updated</td><td>Shipment-data investigation</td></tr><tr><td>Order never reached Seller</td><td>Integration investigation</td></tr><tr><td>Seller unresponsive</td><td>Seller-management escalation</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Enable the daily outstanding-Order summary email under Seller Settings where it supports the operating model. Automated reminders do not replace Operator monitoring.</p><p>Require the Seller to confirm a dispatch commitment, inability to fulfil, missing Shipment update or missing Order integration. Avoid accepting an unowned “looking into it”.</p>","Refund Requests":"<p>Review <strong>Orders → Refund Requests</strong> and prioritise Processed requests, customer payment failures, aged Awaiting requests, returns delivered but not assessed, high-value cases, disputes and refunds affecting payout.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Daily action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller decision required</td><td>Remind or escalate</td></tr><tr><td>Customer return required</td><td>Confirm instructions and tracking</td></tr><tr><td>Returned item delivered</td><td>Obtain Seller assessment</td></tr><tr><td>Processed</td><td>Review financials and finalise</td></tr><tr><td>Denied and disputed</td><td>Apply dispute process</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer Refunded but payment failed</td><td>Resolve payment without another request</td></tr><tr><td>Customer paid externally but Marketplacer incomplete</td><td>Complete and reconcile the existing workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Duplicate suspected</td><td>Stop processing and review prior records</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Refund Request</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Invoice Amendment</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Customer payment refund</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller remittance adjustment</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Customer communication</div></div>","Product Vetting":"<p>Review <strong>Adverts → Product Vetting</strong> for launch blockers, campaign products, resubmissions, ageing products and rule concerns.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Category and Brand</li><li>Title and description</li><li>Images</li><li>Variant options</li><li>Pricing and stock</li><li>Required attributes</li><li>Catalog Rule compliance</li></ul><p>Reject with a clear problem, required correction and correct source system. Do not bulk approve only because the queue is large. Confirm publication and storefront visibility after asynchronous processing.</p>","Failed Integrations":"<p>Review Dashboard Problem Reports, MConnect, webhook event and response history, middleware, storefront, payment and internal incident monitoring.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Flow</th><th>Common impact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product import</td><td>Products missing or outdated</td></tr><tr><td>Price and stock sync</td><td>Incorrect price, oversell or unexpected no stock</td></tr><tr><td>Order creation</td><td>Seller cannot fulfil because the Order is missing</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment sync</td><td>Tracking and status incorrect</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation or refund sync</td><td>Duplicate or incomplete financial workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Payment event</td><td>Order or refund mismatch</td></tr><tr><td>Webhook delivery</td><td>Connected system misses an update</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>For each issue, record environment, Seller, process, first and latest occurrence, failures, object IDs, error, retry history, impact and owner.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not retry blindly.</strong> An apparent failure may have completed in one system or been retried automatically.</div>","Customer Escalations":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Escalation</th><th>Primary owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Order not created</td><td>Technology or Integration</td></tr><tr><td>Seller did not dispatch</td><td>Operations and Seller Management</td></tr><tr><td>Delivery delayed after dispatch</td><td>Customer Service and Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Product issue</td><td>Customer Service and Catalogue</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation or return</td><td>Customer Service or Refund Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Payment or refund failure</td><td>Finance or Payments</td></tr><tr><td>Seller dispute</td><td>Marketplace Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Platform behaviour unclear</td><td>Marketplacer Support</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Confirm the customer Order, Seller Invoice, affected Line Item, fulfilment state, payment state, Refund Request, Seller communication, integration evidence and policy deadline.</p><p>The customer should receive acknowledgement, known facts, current owner, next action and expected update time. Separate immediate customer resolution from root-cause correction.</p>","Seller Communications":"<p>Review Seller chat, shared support inboxes, launch trackers and integration alerts. Use chat for quick operational questions, but use a formal case, ticket or email for payment disputes, repeated performance failure, contractual decisions, complex integrations, suspension or offboarding.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Answered</li><li>Actioned</li><li>Waiting for Seller</li><li>Waiting for Operator</li><li>Escalated</li><li>Converted into tracked work</li><li>Closed</li></ul><p>Do not clear the unread count while leaving the underlying request without an owner.</p>","Payouts and Finance-Critical Work":"<p>Where payout approval is part of the daily model, review <strong>Orders → Payouts to Approve</strong>.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Invoice is complete</li><li>Items were dispatched or cancelled</li><li>No unresolved dispute should hold payment</li><li>Commission and merchant fees are correct</li><li>Refund or amendment activity is understood</li><li>Seller payout details are valid</li></ul><p>Prioritise payment collected but Order missing, failed customer refunds, failed Seller payouts, Processed refunds waiting for payment, suspected duplicates, financial discrepancies and negative Seller balances.</p>","Prioritise by Impact and SLA":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Examples</th><th>Expected response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Critical</td><td>Checkout outage, missing Orders, duplicate payments, failed customer refunds</td><td>Immediate incident response</td></tr><tr><td>High</td><td>SLA-breached dispatch, high-value refund, disabled Seller integration</td><td>Same operating period</td></tr><tr><td>Medium</td><td>Product launch blocker, routine return, mapping backlog</td><td>Within agreed SLA</td></tr><tr><td>Routine</td><td>Standard Product Vetting and non-urgent Seller questions</td><td>Planned queue processing</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use customer count, financial value, age, compliance risk, duplicate risk, campaign dependency and likelihood of spread. Oldest first is not always the correct order.</p>","Record Ownership and Handover":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Tracker field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Issue reference</td><td>Stable ID</td></tr><tr><td>Date identified</td><td>Age and SLA</td></tr><tr><td>Environment and area</td><td>Production or Sandbox; Orders, refunds, products, Finance or integration</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer and external IDs</td><td>Transaction evidence</td></tr><tr><td>Impact and priority</td><td>Customer, Seller, financial or catalogue risk</td></tr><tr><td>Owner and next action</td><td>Accountability</td></tr><tr><td>Due time and status</td><td>Commitment</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence and resolution</td><td>Audit history</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Handover unresolved critical and high-priority issues, customer commitments, Seller responses, Processed refunds, late Orders, unstable integrations, catalogue blockers, payout holds and Support tickets.</p>","Daily Close-Out":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Critical incidents have owners</li><li>Customer refund failures are owned</li><li>Late-dispatch Sellers have been contacted</li><li>Processed refunds are finalised or assigned</li><li>Product Vetting launch blockers are resolved or assigned</li><li>Failed integrations have a current status</li><li>Duplicate-risk transactions are protected from retries</li><li>Customer update commitments have been met</li><li>Seller messages are answered or tracked</li><li>Payout holds have reasons</li><li>Unresolved work is in the handover</li></ul><p>A useful daily summary reports material outcomes across Orders, refunds, catalogue, integrations, customers, Finance, incidents and the next operating period, not only queue counts.</p>","Test Daily Operations":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Each intended role can access its queues</li><li>Dashboard tiles open the correct pages</li><li>A test Order appears in All Sales and Not Dispatched</li><li>Outstanding-Order reminders behave as configured</li><li>Shipment, cancellation and refund workflows update the correct queues</li><li>Customer payment refund is tested</li><li>Product Vetting approval and rejection work</li><li>Problem Reports and webhook evidence can be reviewed</li><li>An MConnect error follows the escalation process</li><li>Duplicate controls work</li><li>Seller chat access is correct</li><li>Payout approval is appropriately restricted</li><li>Operational tracking and handover templates are usable</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Daily monitoring hours and owners are defined</li><li>Incident, dispatch and refund procedures are documented</li><li>Outstanding-Order reminders are configured</li><li>Processed refunds have a finalisation owner</li><li>Customer payment refunds are reconciled</li><li>Product Vetting standards and SLA are documented</li><li>Integration monitoring and fatal-error notifications are active</li><li>Webhook and integration logs are accessible</li><li>Duplicate-processing controls are understood</li><li>Customer escalation priorities are defined</li><li>Seller communication boundaries are documented</li><li>Payout approval has financial controls</li><li>Priority definitions are agreed</li><li>Every unresolved issue receives an owner and deadline</li><li>Shift and daily handovers are established</li><li>Launch and peak-period monitoring frequency is agreed</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360060582452-Operator-daily-tasks-Orders-Adverts-and-Reports\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator daily tasks: Orders, Adverts and Reports</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27307693304333-Operator-welcome-screen-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator welcome screen overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360044027172-Email-reminders-for-non-dispatched-invoices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Email reminders for non-dispatched Invoices</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741316387725-Review-and-approve-products-adverts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and approve products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31442688192269-Refunds-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Refunds Report</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/6646120206733-Integration-error-detection-in-MConnect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Integration error detection in MConnect</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/utility/howto_managewebhooks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Webhooks</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["operator-dashboard","Operator Dashboard"],["weekly-monthly-operations","Weekly and Monthly Operations"],["order-exceptions","Order Exceptions"],["refund-statuses","Refund Statuses"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"]]},"weekly-monthly-operations":{"summary":"Turn daily marketplace activity into structured weekly and monthly reviews that identify Seller risk, catalogue issues, financial exceptions, onboarding blockers, commercial opportunities and recurring incidents.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Seller management","Catalogue","Finance","Customer service","Commercial","Technology","Leadership"],"sections":{"Establish the Operating Cadence":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cadence</th><th>Primary purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Daily</td><td>Resolve urgent Orders, refunds, products, integrations and customer escalations</td></tr><tr><td>Weekly</td><td>Review active performance issues, backlogs, onboarding progress and short-term risks</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly</td><td>Evaluate trends, commercial outcomes, portfolio health, finance and recurring root causes</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Daily operations<br>Resolve immediate issues</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Weekly operations<br>Identify patterns and owners</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Monthly operations<br>Make governance and commercial decisions</div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Do not use the weekly meeting to repeat every daily queue item.</strong> Use it to review trends, breaches, blocked work and cross-functional decisions.</div>","Prepare the Review Pack":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Review area</th><th>Recommended source</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace Sales</td><td>Performance Insights, Sales Report or All Sales</td></tr><tr><td>Seller performance</td><td>Sellers → Seller Performance</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue health</td><td>Product Vetting, Search Adverts and Mapping</td></tr><tr><td>Orders and fulfilment</td><td>All Sales, Not Dispatched and Seller Performance</td></tr><tr><td>Refunds</td><td>Refund Requests and Refunds Report</td></tr><tr><td>Remittances</td><td>Processed and Unprocessed Remittances</td></tr><tr><td>Seller onboarding</td><td>Onboarding tracker and launch checklist</td></tr><tr><td>Integration health</td><td>Problem Reports, MConnect, webhooks and middleware</td></tr><tr><td>Incidents</td><td>Incident register and Support tickets</td></tr><tr><td>Actions</td><td>Previous action register</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Record environment, period, timezone, extraction date, sources, filters, definitions, exclusions, reporting delays and owner. Align period, scope, grain and refund treatment before comparing results.</p>","Run the Weekly Operations Review":"<p>The weekly review focuses on active marketplace health and the next seven to fourteen days.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Agenda</th><th>Focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Previous actions</td><td>Overdue and blocked commitments</td></tr><tr><td>Customer and Order risks</td><td>Late fulfilment, refunds and escalations</td></tr><tr><td>Seller performance</td><td>Breaches, cancellations, returns and tracking</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue quality</td><td>Vetting, rejections, rules, mapping and stock</td></tr><tr><td>Seller onboarding</td><td>Pipeline, blockers and launch dates</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Refund exceptions, remittance blockers and payouts</td></tr><tr><td>Sales and assortment</td><td>Trend, Seller contribution and opportunities</td></tr><tr><td>Integrations</td><td>Failures, disabled connections and reconciliation</td></tr><tr><td>Decisions</td><td>Owner, due date and expected outcome</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Every material issue must leave the meeting resolved, accepted and monitored, assigned with a deadline, escalated, converted into a project or incident, or closed with a documented decision.</p>","Seller Performance Review":"<p>Use Seller Performance to review new and repeated dispatch breaches, cancellations, returns, missing tracking, customer escalations, unstable integrations and active corrective plans.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller context</th><th>Required interpretation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Low-volume high rate</td><td>Review absolute event count and customer impact</td></tr><tr><td>High-volume lower rate</td><td>Review the total affected customers</td></tr><tr><td>Repeated target miss</td><td>Move into corrective action</td></tr><tr><td>Strong sustained performance</td><td>Recognise and share good practice</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use 30 days for current performance, 90 days for stability and year to date for governance. The weekly rating can lag the current week’s actions.</p><p>Record the metric, affected records, root cause, Seller response, action, owner, due date and next review.</p>","Catalogue Quality Review":"<p>Review Product Vetting, Search Adverts, Recently updated, Mapping and Seller integration errors.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Weekly question</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Awaiting vetting</td><td>Is the queue growing or ageing?</td></tr><tr><td>Approved and rejected</td><td>Is throughput and submission quality acceptable?</td></tr><tr><td>Repeated rejections</td><td>Does the Seller need training or source correction?</td></tr><tr><td>Failed Catalog Rules</td><td>Which rules or Sellers drive failure?</td></tr><tr><td>Unmapped values</td><td>Which launches or Categories are blocked?</td></tr><tr><td>Online and stocked products</td><td>How much assortment is purchasable?</td></tr><tr><td>Recently updated risks</td><td>Did live pricing, Category, Brand or image changes require action?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Monthly, review catalogue-ready rate, Category and Brand coverage, product and Variant growth, assortment concentration, rule effectiveness, duplicates and inactive products.</p>","Finance Reconciliation":"<p>Weekly Finance review focuses on exceptions and short-term cash movement. Monthly Finance review reconciles the complete period.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Customer payment and refund failures</li><li>Processed refunds awaiting finalisation</li><li>Payout approvals and unprocessed remittance reasons</li><li>Negative Seller balances</li><li>Remittance Advices awaiting actual payment</li><li>Commission and merchant-fee discrepancies</li><li>Missing Invoice Amendments</li><li>Payout or bank mismatches</li></ul><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Marketplacer Sales</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Customer payment gateway</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Refunds and Invoice Amendments</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Commission and merchant fees</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Remittance Advices</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller payouts</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Accounting ledger</div></div><p>Record unmatched value, owner, expected resolution and Finance approval. Do not close a period only because the difference is small.</p>","Seller Onboarding Pipeline":"<div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Commercially agreed</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Information collected</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Seller account and configuration</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Technical connection</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Products imported</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Mapping and quality</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">End-to-end testing</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Launch ready</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Live</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Hypercare</div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Exit requirement</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Commercially agreed</td><td>Agreement and model confirmed</td></tr><tr><td>Information collection</td><td>Legal, business, operational and technical data received</td></tr><tr><td>Account setup</td><td>Seller and users created</td></tr><tr><td>Configuration</td><td>Commission, remittance, shipping and permissions confirmed</td></tr><tr><td>Technical connection</td><td>MConnect, API, bulk or Portal method ready</td></tr><tr><td>Product ingestion</td><td>Sample or live products imported</td></tr><tr><td>Mapping and quality</td><td>Values mapped, rules passed and vetting ready</td></tr><tr><td>Testing</td><td>Product, stock, Order, fulfilment and refund tested</td></tr><tr><td>Launch ready</td><td>Products approved, payout ready and contacts trained</td></tr><tr><td>Live and hypercare</td><td>First activity monitored</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>For each Seller, record stage, target launch, next milestone, blocker, owner, product counts, mapping, vetting, testing, payout and training readiness. Monthly, review launch throughput, time in stage, recurring blockers and pipeline capacity.</p>","Sales and Assortment Review":"<p>Use Sales reporting and catalogue data together.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Questions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace growth</td><td>Are Sales, Orders and commission growing?</td></tr><tr><td>Seller contribution</td><td>Which Sellers drive value and which are inactive?</td></tr><tr><td>Category performance</td><td>Which Categories grow, decline or return frequently?</td></tr><tr><td>Assortment depth</td><td>Are important Categories sufficiently ranged?</td></tr><tr><td>Stock availability</td><td>Are strong-selling products consistently available?</td></tr><tr><td>Seller concentration</td><td>Is the marketplace overdependent on a few Sellers?</td></tr><tr><td>Pipeline contribution</td><td>Will incoming Sellers close assortment gaps?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Product count alone is not enough. Combine live stocked products, Sales, refunds, commission and Category productivity.</p>","Incident Review":"<p>Weekly incident review confirms active incidents and complete recovery. Monthly review identifies recurring causes and preventive actions.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Storefront</td><td>Visibility, checkout and Order submission</td></tr><tr><td>Product integration</td><td>Imports, mapping, price, stock and images</td></tr><tr><td>Order integration</td><td>Missing or duplicate Orders</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment</td><td>Shipment and tracking updates</td></tr><tr><td>Refunds and payments</td><td>Incomplete or duplicate money movement</td></tr><tr><td>Remittances</td><td>Missing or incorrect payout records</td></tr><tr><td>Webhooks</td><td>Delivery, authentication or consumer failures</td></tr><tr><td>Access</td><td>Login and permissions</td></tr><tr><td>Platform</td><td>Marketplacer service incident</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"structure-diagram\"><div class=\"structure-node\">Service restored</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Backlog processed</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Affected records reconciled</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Customers and Sellers updated</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Root cause recorded</div><div class=\"structure-arrow\">↓</div><div class=\"structure-node\">Preventive action assigned</div></div><p>Use consistent root-cause categories so monthly reporting can identify investment and process priorities.</p>","Run the Monthly Marketplace Review":"<p>The monthly meeting makes decisions about marketplace health and direction.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Executive performance summary</li><li>Seller portfolio performance</li><li>Sales and commission</li><li>Refund and customer-experience trends</li><li>Catalogue and assortment health</li><li>Seller onboarding pipeline</li><li>Finance reconciliation and Seller balances</li><li>Incidents and platform risk</li><li>Capacity and workload</li><li>Decisions and actions</li></ul><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Example measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Sales</td><td>Total Sales and Orders</td></tr><tr><td>Commercial</td><td>Net commission</td></tr><tr><td>Sellers</td><td>Active trading Sellers</td></tr><tr><td>Operations</td><td>Dispatch breach, cancellation and return rates</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Online stocked products and catalogue-ready rate</td></tr><tr><td>Onboarding</td><td>Sellers launched</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Unreconciled value</td></tr><tr><td>Incidents</td><td>Customer-impacting incidents</td></tr><tr><td>Actions</td><td>Overdue governance actions</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Configuration changes arising from the review must follow testing, approval and change control rather than being applied directly from the meeting.</p>","Maintain the Action Register":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Action ID</td><td>Stable reference</td></tr><tr><td>Review date and area</td><td>Context</td></tr><tr><td>Issue and decision</td><td>Problem and approved response</td></tr><tr><td>Owner and contributors</td><td>Accountability</td></tr><tr><td>Due date and priority</td><td>Commitment</td></tr><tr><td>Status</td><td>Open, Blocked, Monitoring or Complete</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence and outcome</td><td>Closure proof</td></tr><tr><td>Closure date</td><td>Audit record</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Every action requires one accountable owner, one specific outcome, one due date and one closure condition. Review overdue actions first and escalate repeated non-completion.</p>","Understand Reporting Periods and Data Freshness":"<p>Different reports update on different cycles, including weekly Seller ratings, nightly remittance processing, asynchronous product publication, near-real-time operational queues and complete-day Performance Insights.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Label every metric with source and last refresh</li><li>Record reporting period and timezone</li><li>Confirm transaction grain</li><li>State whether the period is complete</li><li>State whether refunds and first-party products are included</li><li>Retain period-end raw extracts</li></ul><p>A current Portal view cannot always recreate the exact state that existed at a previous month end.</p>","Test the Operating Cadence":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Review owners can access the required reports</li><li>Reporting periods are applied consistently</li><li>Seller Performance data can be exported</li><li>Product Vetting and Search Adverts queues can be reviewed</li><li>Catalogue product and Variant counts are interpreted correctly</li><li>Finance reports reconcile to payment and payout records</li><li>Unprocessed remittance reasons can be identified</li><li>Seller onboarding stages and exit requirements are understood</li><li>Sales and assortment measures use agreed definitions</li><li>Incidents include full recovery and reconciliation</li><li>Actions have one owner and due date</li><li>Raw extracts are retained</li><li>Production and Sandbox data are not mixed</li></ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Weekly and monthly owners, attendees and decision authority are agreed</li><li>Review periods and marketplace timezone are documented</li><li>The core reporting pack and definitions are approved</li><li>Seller performance standards and low-volume treatment are documented</li><li>Catalogue-ready and live-stocked definitions are agreed</li><li>Finance reconciliation and negative-balance treatment are documented</li><li>Seller onboarding stages and exit criteria are defined</li><li>Every Seller has a target launch date and next action</li><li>Sales and assortment reporting uses the correct grain</li><li>Incidents remain open until reconciliation is complete</li><li>Root-cause categories are standardised</li><li>Raw weekly and monthly extracts are retained</li><li>The action register has ownership and escalation</li><li>Configuration decisions follow testing and change control</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599850695821-Intro-to-the-Seller-Performance-dashboard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Intro to the Seller Performance dashboard</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25571003783309-Seller-metrics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller metrics</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599997635341-Export-SLA-seller-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Export SLA Seller data</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741316387725-Review-and-approve-products-adverts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and approve products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27467503428237-Reviewing-vetted-and-approved-products-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Reviewing vetted and approved products and Variants</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14369804027661\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Access to data for Analysis</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14369744945933-Introduction-to-Marketplace-analytics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Introduction to Marketplace analytics</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27307693304333-Operator-welcome-screen-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator welcome screen overview</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["daily-operations","Daily Marketplace Operations"],["seller-performance-reporting","Seller Performance Reporting"],["catalogue-reporting","Catalogue Reporting"],["finance-reporting-operations","Finance Reporting"],["sales-reporting","Sales Reporting"]]}};
